---
title: Spanish One-Pan Chicken with Chorizo and Bell Peppers
description: In Spain, paella is something of a festive dish, made for large gatherings or celebrations and almost always cooked over a wood fire. Don't tell the Spaniards, but we think it's also a pretty great, quick and easy, one-pan stovetop recipe that can be enjoyed even in cozy and intimate settings. Filled with chicken, chorizo, and bright red peppers, our version feels like a meaty, savory, flavor-filled jubilee.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/spanish-one-pot-chicken-7dc5fcf4.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/spanish-one-pot-chicken-46b8b3ac.pdf
servings: 2
course: main course
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spanish-one-pan-chicken-582c97682e69d7666b64ed42
nutrition:
  calories: 529 kcal
  fat: 14 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 54 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 50 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 706 mg
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: Spanish
---

Wash and dry all produce. Core, seed, and thinly slice @Red Bell Pepper{1}(thinly sliced). Halve, peel, and dice @Yellow Onion{1}(diced). Mince or grate @Garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Slice @Dried Chorizo{2%ounce} into 1/4-inch-thick rounds.

Heat a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add chorizo to pan and cook until it crisps and releases some of its oil, ~{1-2%minutes} per side. Set aside, leaving oil in pan.

Season @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} on all sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat same pan over medium heat. Add a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}. Add chicken and sear until browned and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside.

> TIP: If pan seems dry, add a drizzle of oil.

Add onion, garlic, bell peppers, and a drizzle of oil to same pan over medium heat. Stir until just softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add @Basmati Rice{1/2%cup} and stir to coat. Stir in @water{1%cup}, a pinch of salt, and @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1%unit}. Cover and reduce heat to low. Simmer until rice is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut @Lemon{1} into wedges. Finely chop @Parsley{1/4%ounce}(chopped).

> TIP: While you wait for rice to finish, try practicing this Spanish phrase: Con pan y vino se anda el camino (life is better with food and wine).

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season generously with salt and pepper. Place chicken on top and sprinkle with crispy chorizo. Remove pan from heat and sprinkle with parsley and a few squeezes of lemon.